    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Pre-Columbian culture and period of the Central Andes, marked by the expansion of irrigation on the coast and and development of a lake-agricultural-livestock economy; focused on southern shore of Lake Titicaca, and population center at Chiripa, Bolivia. The culture is temporally located between the between the Initial period and Early Horizon period.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
